AGI - Two Italian skiers died in an accident on Thursday on the Abisko mountains, Sweden, where a helicopter was overwhelmed by an avalanche.&nbsp;
The Farnesina has confirmed that "in yesterday afternoon a heliskiing accident occurred in the extreme North of Sweden with 3 Italian brothers of Luserna San Giuseppe involved.> Two of them died. The third is returned to the starting resort, Niehku, in the region of Abisko near the border with Norway" reads in a note. "The Italian Embassy in Sweden is in contact with the relatives of the compatriots involved and will follow the procedures for the return to Italy of the dead skiers". &nbsp;
According to the reconstructions of the local media, an avalanche fell on a still helicopter that was overwhelmed. On site there was a group of five Italian skiers, led by an IFMGA certified alpine guide internationally.
The mountain guide and the two brothers were overwhelmed by the avalanche. The two were buried under the snow, while the guide remained on the surface, wrote the tourist agency Niehku Mountain Villas in a press release. On the site of the incident came shortly after a medical team and alpine rescue. A third person is injured but his condition is not clear.
